132
00:07:42,128 --> 00:07:45,063
Oh! Wow, so then that
nasty yellow goop is...

133
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:47,827
<i>Fat. 9.3 liters so far.</i>

134
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:50,528
Oh, good. Booth, I'm sure
you'll want to see this too.

135
00:07:51,904 --> 00:07:54,668
- <i>What is it?</i>
- Guess?

136
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:57,368
- Maybe not, Zack.
- It's our victim's wallet.

137
00:07:57,443 --> 00:07:59,502
Can you believe it?
Leather, cash, cards...

138
00:07:59,579 --> 00:08:02,707
every shred of identification
completely emulsified.

139
00:08:02,782 --> 00:08:06,741
Mmm, wow. You know what, Zack?
I'd like to go back to the old arrangement...

140
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:08,878
where you don't talk
to me directly, okay?

141
00:08:08,955 --> 00:08:11,253
<i>Have my water sifters arrived yet?</i>

142
00:08:11,324 --> 00:08:14,384
- Yes. That's how I found the wallet.
- Okay, so the point of this is?

143
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:18,726
Doing what that wallet can't.
Right now, I'd say our victim's an ectomorph.

144
00:08:18,798 --> 00:08:21,266
Thin, linear, narrow features.

145
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:23,234
And I hear you're back with your ex.

146
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:27,701
- I'm sorry?
- Rebecca, right?

147
00:08:27,773 --> 00:08:30,037
- Reliving old times?
- [Chuckles]

148
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:35,213
Uh, I'll just keep sifting.

149
00:08:35,281 --> 00:08:38,478
- Yeah. Dr. Brennan told you?
- Oh, relax.

150
00:08:38,551 --> 00:08:40,815
- She did, didn't she?
- We all have our weak moments.

151
00:08:40,887 --> 00:08:44,721
No. Mm-mmm.
We don't, okay?

152
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:46,724
- I don't.
- Please, Seeley.

153
00:08:46,792 --> 00:08:49,818
Like we haven't shared enough
of them for me to know better.

154
00:08:52,298 --> 00:08:54,391
- <i>[Brennan] I was not gossiping.</i>
- Oh, really?

155
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:56,401
