184
00:10:13,412 --> 00:10:17,178
This is usually where I type and you talk.
You two are never not talking.

185
00:10:17,249 --> 00:10:19,149
Well, we're not not talking.

186
00:10:19,218 --> 00:10:22,210
Or maybe we're not not... not.

187
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:24,256
Okeydoke.

188
00:10:24,323 --> 00:10:26,314
Number of adult males with brittle bone...

189
00:10:26,392 --> 00:10:28,417
in the metropolitan area is...

190
00:10:28,494 --> 00:10:31,691
<i>zero... same with adult females.</i>

191
00:10:31,764 --> 00:10:34,392
- These are all kids.
- Why is that? High mortality rate?

192
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:37,903
No. When O.I. is fatal,
it's mainly to infants.

193
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:41,235
- And only in severe cases.
- So our guy has a mild case.

194
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:43,332
Type I.
Near normal stature...

195
00:10:43,409 --> 00:10:46,173
<i>fragile bones andjoints,</i>
<i>off-white sclera.</i>

196
00:10:46,245 --> 00:10:49,510
- Is this disease hereditary?
- Mild cases can be.

197
00:10:49,582 --> 00:10:52,278
The more severe forms,
types II and III...

198
00:10:52,351 --> 00:10:54,581
are often the result
of a genetic mutation.

199
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:58,112
But if our guy is type I and these kids
got it passed on from a parent...

200
00:10:58,190 --> 00:11:00,886
Then all we have to do is
contact these kids' families...

201
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:03,360
and find out which one
is missing a dad.

202
00:11:03,429 --> 00:11:06,956
